5.2 Mutually exclusive if() statement
Since the two if() statements above (Figure 4 and Figure 5) have mutually exclusive conditions and use the exact some for loop, we can (and should) combine them into one if-else-if statement.  The following code is functionally the same but more efficient (i.e., faster):



for(i in 1:numDays)
{
  if(highTemps[i] &gt; 60 & noonCond[i] == "Sunny")
  {
    cat("day", i, " good day to go out\n");
